  "body": "# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nIf the beacon node API is accessible on the internet then an attacker can perform a range-based DoS attack using `/eth/v1/validator/duties/attester/`.\r\n\r\nThe documents https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/how-prysm-works/ethereum-public-api and https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/how-prysm-works/ethereum-public-api don't contain warnings that Prysm Beacon Node API shouldn't be exposed to untrusted parties. \r\n\r\nAt the same time, Prysm uses TLS to provide server-side authentication and encryption.\r\n\r\nSee also:\r\n- https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/2468\r\n\r\nAt least we suggest adding the warning to the documentation.\r\n### Description\r\nSince TLS is already [used](https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/prysm-usage/secure-grpc/) it would be great to add optional certificate-based client-side authentication for customers deploying the nodes on clouds or the internet.\r\n\r\n",
